# Grandfathered endpoints that do not return ApiResponse[T].
# Format: <repo-relative-file>:<function-name> (line-independent).
# Empty line OK. # comments OK.
#
# A line here means "this endpoint pre-dates the envelope contract; do not
# block PRs that touch it for envelope reasons. NEW endpoints must conform."

# articles_export.py:start_export returns `Response | ApiResponse[T]` — the
# Union arm makes the check's AST matcher (which expects a Subscript
# ApiResponse[...]) reject it. Legitimate: the endpoint can stream a binary
# Response OR an envelope. Tightening the check to recognise the Union form
# is a Phase-2 improvement to check_api_response_envelope.py itself.
backend/app/api/v1/endpoints/articles_export.py:start_export
